The exmaple show the interactive Qt application that combines the the example:
http://artis.imag.fr/Members/Gilles.Debunne/QGLViewer/examples/animation.html 
and the ROOT TCanvas with 2D histogram to represent the particles "speed vs position".

It requires QGLViewer package to be installed. 
The package is included into the QtRoot-Extension distribution
To run the example against of the CERN dustribtuion please download and install QGLViewer
http://artis.imag.fr/Software/QGLViewer/download.html

   1. Download and unpack the Qt project directory:
      "http://root.bnl.gov/QtRoot/downloads/qtRootProject.tar.gz"
      For example use "wget"
      "wget http://root.bnl.gov/QtRoot/downloads/qtRootProject.tar.gz"
     
   2. "Un-tar" the archive
       tar -xzvf qtRootProject.tar.gz
      
   3. To create the your platform makefile:
      "rm -rf .rootrc"  -- Unix ONLY
      "qmake"
      Attention. One may require to change the  HelloGLViewer.pro
      ---------  to edit the QGLViewer  installation directory
      
   4. To build the application type:
      Unix:
         "make"
      Windows ( no Cygwin!!! ):
         "nmake"    
      
      
   5. To start the example
      " HelloGLViewer"
      
  
